Review: My favorite brewery in the city! Excellent options whether you’re into sours, IPAs, or stouts. Doesn’t hurt that they have some arcade games and picnic tables for large groups!
Affordable option for a decent quick burger. Nothing crazy but it delivers
Food was amazing. Unfortunately all 4 in my group got food poisoning the next morning…
One of the best meals of my life (and it better be for the price)!
Fire sushi spot with excellent nigiri!
Favorite ice cream spot in town! Unique flavors and way underrated (i think smitten’s gets too much love tbh)

This was an expensive, 2 michellin star restaurant that is likely best reserved for special occasions. HOWEVER, as a self- described carnivore I have NEVER enjoyed vegetables so much. Definitely a top 5 meal in my LIFE. Excellent service too and extremely accommodating for allergies!
Possibly the best croissants in the city and everyone is sleeping on them. Coffee is not the best tho. But the croissants are worth it!
Great french bakery spot with a wide array of breakfast, lunch, and coffee options.
If i had to choose a pizza spot in SF, it’d be Tony’s. The giant meatballs are an underrated extra option (great for sharing!)
